MAPPING.DESCRIPTION: Apply transmitted distribution transactions back to Recon Extended Claims.

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: Update Recon Extended Claims with transmitted transaction data.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: UPD_Update_Extended_Clms

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: -- OVERRIDE SQL used -- Added as part of ITPR017177 - CV Rewrite Project: -- pending adjustment and distributios are hardcoded as 0 since post-apc can only send the invoice changes. adjustment and distribution amounts are available only for dropped claims. post apc claim when dropped and added back, transmission will remove the adjustments that was already on that, and the user distribution follwed by snap will take care of sending the adjustments back to SAP and RPS. In order to updated the distribution adjustments: it will updated only when completly dropped claims, dropped claims added back, retained claims with value changes. when invoice change is same as the invoice amount and any of the pending amounts are not equals to 0 or all pending amounts are 0 and dsadj amount also 0 then it will update the amount difference between pending invoice and apc amounts, if not then it will update the only pending invoice amounts on extended claim table.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: SQ_PostAPC_Clms

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE:
SELECT STG.DSTR_GID AS DSTR_DSTR_GID, STG.RECN_GID AS DSTR_RECN_GID, STG.HVST_ID AS DSTR_HVST_ID, STG.INV_ID AS DSTR_INV_ID, STG.CLM_GID AS DSTR_CLM_GID,
CASE WHEN ((STG.ADMN_PEND_INV_AMT = EXTN.ADMN_DISCNT_AMT) AND ((STG.ADMN_PEND_INV_AMT<>0 or STG.ADMN_PEND_ADJ_AMT<>0 or STG.ADMN_PEND_DSTR_AMT<>0) OR (STG.ADMN_PEND_INV_AMT=0 and STG.ADMN_PEND_ADJ_AMT=0 and STG.ADMN_PEND_DSTR_AMT=0 and EXTN.ADMN_DISC_DSADJ_AMT =0))) THEN STG.ADMN_PEND_INV_AMT-EXTN.ADMN_DISC_APC_AMT ELSE STG.ADMN_PEND_INV_AMT END AS DSTR_ADMN_PEND_INV_AMT, 0 AS DSTR_ADMN_PEND_ADJ_AMT, 0 AS DSTR_ADMN_PEND_DSTR_AMT, CASE WHEN ((STG.BASE_PEND_INV_AMT = EXTN.BASE_DISCNT_AMT) AND ((STG.BASE_PEND_INV_AMT<>0 or STG.BASE_PEND_ADJ_AMT<>0 or STG.BASE_PEND_DSTR_AMT<>0) OR (STG.BASE_PEND_INV_AMT=0 and STG.BASE_PEND_ADJ_AMT=0 and STG.BASE_PEND_DSTR_AMT=0 and EXTN.BASE_DISC_DSADJ_AMT =0))) THEN STG.BASE_PEND_INV_AMT-EXTN.BASE_DISC_APC_AMT ELSE STG.BASE_PEND_INV_AMT END AS DSTR_BASE_PEND_INV_AMT,
0 AS DSTR_BASE_PEND_ADJ_AMT, 0 AS DSTR_BASE_PEND_DSTR_AMT, CASE WHEN ((STG.FRMLY_PEND_INV_AMT = EXTN.FRMLY_DISCNT_AMT) AND ((STG.FRMLY_PEND_INV_AMT<>0 OR STG.FRMLY_PEND_ADJ_AMT<>0 OR STG.FRMLY_PEND_DSTR_AMT<>0) OR (STG.FRMLY_PEND_INV_AMT=0 and STG.FRMLY_PEND_ADJ_AMT=0 and STG.FRMLY_PEND_DSTR_AMT=0 and EXTN.FRMLY_DISC_DSADJ_AMT=0))) THEN STG.FRMLY_PEND_INV_AMT-EXTN.FRMLY_DISC_APC_AMT ELSE STG.FRMLY_PEND_INV_AMT END AS DSTR_FRMLY_PEND_INV_AMT,
0 AS DSTR_FRMLY_PEND_ADJ_AMT, 0 AS DSTR_FRMLY_PEND_DSTR_AMT, CASE WHEN ((STG.CTRC_PEND_INV_AMT = EXTN.CNTRCT_DISCNT_AMT) AND ((STG.CTRC_PEND_INV_AMT<>0 OR STG.CTRC_PEND_ADJ_AMT<>0 OR STG.CTRC_PEND_DSTR_AMT<>0) OR (STG.CTRC_PEND_INV_AMT=0 AND STG.CTRC_PEND_ADJ_AMT=0 AND STG.CTRC_PEND_DSTR_AMT=0 AND EXTN.CTRC_DISC_DSADJ_AMT=0 ))) THEN STG.CTRC_PEND_INV_AMT-EXTN.CTRC_DISC_APC_AMT ELSE STG.CTRC_PEND_INV_AMT END AS DSTR_CTRC_PEND_INV_AMT,
0 AS DSTR_CTRC_PEND_ADJ_AMT, 0 AS DSTR_CTRC_PEND_DSTR_AMT, CASE WHEN ((STG.PERF_PEND_INV_AMT = EXTN.PRFMC_DISCNT_AMT) AND ((STG.PERF_PEND_INV_AMT<>0 OR STG.PERF_PEND_ADJ_AMT<>0 OR STG.PERF_PEND_DSTR_AMT<>0) OR (STG.PERF_PEND_INV_AMT=0 AND STG.PERF_PEND_ADJ_AMT=0 AND STG.PERF_PEND_DSTR_AMT=0 AND EXTN.PERF_DISC_DSADJ_AMT=0 ))) THEN STG.PERF_PEND_INV_AMT-EXTN.PERF_DISC_APC_AMT ELSE STG.PERF_PEND_INV_AMT END AS DSTR_CTRC_PEND_INV_AMT,
0 AS DSTR_PERF_PEND_ADJ_AMT, 0 AS DSTR_PERF_PEND_DSTR_AMT, CASE WHEN ((STG.PRC_PTCT_PEND_INV_AMT = EXTN.PRC_PTCT_DISCNT_AMT) AND ((STG.PRC_PTCT_PEND_INV_AMT<>0 OR STG.PRC_PTCT_PEND_ADJ_AMT<>0 OR STG.PRC_PTCT_PEND_DSTR_AMT <>0) OR (STG.PRC_PTCT_PEND_INV_AMT=0 and STG.PRC_PTCT_PEND_ADJ_AMT=0 and STG.PRC_PTCT_PEND_DSTR_AMT =0 and EXTN.PRC_PTCT_DSADJ_DISC_AMT=0 ))) THEN STG.PRC_PTCT_PEND_INV_AMT-EXTN.PRC_PTCT_DISC_APC_AMT ELSE STG.PRC_PTCT_PEND_INV_AMT END AS DSTR_CTRC_PEND_INV_AMT,
0 AS DSTR_PRC_PTCT_PEND_ADJ_AMT , 0 AS DSTR_PRC_PTCT_PEND_DSTR_AMT, EXTN.RECN_ERR_CD, EXTN.ADMN_DISC_DSADJ_AMT, EXTN.BASE_DISC_DSADJ_AMT, EXTN.PERF_DISC_DSADJ_AMT, EXTN.FRMLY_DISC_DSADJ_AMT, EXTN.CTRC_DISC_DSADJ_AMT, EXTN.PRC_PTCT_DSADJ_DISC_AMT, EXTN.ADMN_DISC_DSMCH_AMT, EXTN.BASE_DISC_DSMCH_AMT, EXTN.PERF_DISC_DSMCH_AMT, EXTN.FRMLY_DISC_DSMCH_AMT, EXTN.CTRC_DISC_DSMCH_AMT, EXTN.PRC_PTCT_DSMCH_DISC_AMT FROM VRAP.RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR HDR, VRAP.RCNT_RECN_DSTR_TXN_STG STG, VRAP.RCNT_RECN_EXTN_CLM EXTN WHERE HDR.DSTR_STAT_CD = 15 AND HDR.DSTR_CRTE_TYP_CD = 5 AND HDR.DSTR_GID = STG.DSTR_GID AND STG.RECN_ERR_CD <> 90 AND STG.RECN_GID = EXTN.RECN_GID AND STG.HVST_ID = EXTN.HVST_ID AND STG.INV_ID = EXTN.INV_ID AND STG.CLM_GID = EXTN.CLM_GID and EXTN.RECN_SCRB_CD <>99 with ur

All the Pending columns are set to Zero [NOTE: These will already be zero for Snapshots] Build Insert data for Recon Extended Claims Audit. Any column that is updated on Recon Extended Claims is populated. All the rest are left NULL. Build Update data for Recon Stage Claims Set the Recon Error Code to 90 to facilitate re-runs, if necessary.

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: select recn.RECN_GID from (select eclm.RECN_GID , sum(case when eclm.ADMN_DISC_MTCH_AMT = eclm.ADMN_DISC_DSMCH_AMT and eclm.ADMN_DISCNT_AMT+eclm.ADMN_DISC_ADJ_AMT = eclm.ADMN_DISC_APC_AMT+eclm.ADMN_DISC_DSADJ_AMT and eclm.ADMN_DISC_APC_AMT+eclm.ADMN_DISC_DSADJ_AMT = eclm.ADMN_DISC_DSMCH_AMT and eclm.BASE_DISC_MTCH_AMT = eclm.BASE_DISC_DSMCH_AMT and eclm.BASE_DISCNT_AMT+eclm.BASE_DISC_ADJ_AMT = eclm.BASE_DISC_APC_AMT+eclm.BASE_DISC_DSADJ_AMT and eclm.BASE_DISC_APC_AMT+eclm.BASE_DISC_DSADJ_AMT = eclm.BASE_DISC_DSMCH_AMT and eclm.PERF_DISC_MTCH_AMT = eclm.PERF_DISC_DSMCH_AMT and eclm.PRFMC_DISCNT_AMT+eclm.PERF_DISC_ADJ_AMT = eclm.PERF_DISC_APC_AMT+eclm.PERF_DISC_DSADJ_AMT and eclm.PERF_DISC_APC_AMT+eclm.PERF_DISC_DSADJ_AMT = eclm.PERF_DISC_DSMCH_AMT and eclm.FRMLY_DISC_MTCH_AMT = eclm.FRMLY_DISC_DSMCH_AMT and eclm.FRMLY_DISCNT_AMT+eclm.FRMLY_DISC_ADJ_AMT = eclm.FRMLY_DISC_APC_AMT+eclm.FRMLY_DISC_DSADJ_AMT and eclm.FRMLY_DISC_APC_AMT+eclm.FRMLY_DISC_DSADJ_AMT = eclm.FRMLY_DISC_DSMCH_AMT and eclm.CTRC_DISC_MTCH_AMT = eclm.CTRC_DISC_DSMCH_AMT and eclm.CNTRCT_DISCNT_AMT+eclm.CTRC_DISC_ADJ_AMT = eclm.CTRC_DISC_APC_AMT+eclm.CTRC_DISC_DSADJ_AMT and eclm.CTRC_DISC_APC_AMT+eclm.CTRC_DISC_DSADJ_AMT = eclm.CTRC_DISC_DSMCH_AMT and eclm.PRC_PTCT_MTCH_DISC_AMT = eclm.PRC_PTCT_DSMCH_DISC_AMT and eclm.PRC_PTCT_DISCNT_AMT+eclm.PRC_PTCT_DISC_ADJ_AMT = eclm.PRC_PTCT_DISC_APC_AMT+eclm.PRC_PTCT_DSADJ_DISC_AMT and eclm.PRC_PTCT_DISC_APC_AMT+eclm.PRC_PTCT_DSADJ_DISC_AMT = eclm.PRC_PTCT_DSMCH_DISC_AMT then 0 else 1 end) NONBAL from vrap.rcnt_recn_dstr_hdr dstr , vrap.rcnt_recn_extn_clm eclm where dstr.DSTR_STAT_CD=15 and dstr.DSTR_CRTE_TYP_CD=11 and dstr.RECN_GID not in (select distinct xdstr.RECN_GID from vrap.rcnt_recn_dstr_hdr xdstr left join vrap.rcnt_recn_dspt xdspt on coalesce(xdspt.RSL_REAS_CD,0)=0 and xdspt.RECN_GID=xdstr.RECN_GID where xdstr.DSTR_STAT_CD=15 and xdstr.DSTR_CRTE_TYP_CD=11 and xdspt.RECN_GID is NOT NULL) and dstr.RECN_GID=eclm.RECN_GID and eclm.RECN_SCRB_CD<>99 group by eclm.RECN_GID ) recn where recn.NONBAL=0

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: 9 --Complete
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: RECN_STAT_CD

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: Get Snapshots that do NOT have distributions. Their status will be set to 90=Completed.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: SQ_TSNAP1

TABLEATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
TABLEATTRIBUTE.VALUE: select s.SNAP_ID from vrap.TSNAP s left join vrap.RCNT_RECN_DSTR_HDR d on d.PRCS_CRTE_ID = s.SNAP_ID where s.SNAP_XMIT_STAT_CD = 15 and d.DSTR_GID is NULL

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This Snapshot had NO distributions to process. Just set as completed.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: EXP_Set_Completed

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: 90 --Completed
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: SNAP_XMIT_STAT_CD

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: This was added for ITPR0001971, the users requested that we capture the snapshot transmission time.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: EXP_Format_Update

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: Aggregate to Distributed Snapshots, obtaining a count of: (1) associated Distribution Headers in 90=Completed Status (2) 99=Error Status or (3) any other status
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: AGG_Snapshot

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION:
SUM(NOT IN(DSTR_STAT_CD,90,99))
-- If Distribution Status Code not 90 or 99, then add to count ---- otherwise, do not. -- IN function returns 1 if Status Code in list. ---- Since we want to know if not in list, use NOT
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: DSTR_STAT_OTHER_CNT

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION:
SUM(IN(DSTR_STAT_CD,99))
-- If Distribution Status Code 99 [Error] add to count ---- otherwise, do not. -- IN function returns 1 if Status Code in list; otherwise 0.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: DSTR_STAT_ERROR_CNT

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION:
SUM(IN(DSTR_STAT_CD,90))
-- If Distribution Status Code 90 [Complete] add to count ---- otherwise, do not. -- IN function returns 1 if Status Code in list; otherwise 0.
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: DSTR_STAT_COMPL_CNT

TRANSFORMATION.DESCRIPTION: If ANY Distribution Header associated with the Snapshot is in status other than 90=Complete or 99=Error, do not change the staus of the Snapshot. If ALL of the associated Distribution Headers are Complete or Error, but at least one Error, then set as Error. If ALL of the asscciated Distribution Headers are in Complete Status, then set to Complete.
TRANSFORMATION.NAME: EXP_Determine_Status

TRANSFORMFIELD.EXPRESSION: IIF(DSTR_STAT_OTHER_CNT > 0 , SNAP_XMIT_STAT_CD_in --Still processing. No change , IIF(DSTR_STAT_ERROR_CNT > 0 , 99 --None processing, but errors found. Set to Error. , 90 --None processing, all completed. Set Completed. ) )
TRANSFORMFIELD.NAME: vSNAP_XMIT_STAT_CD
